# Background
- multiple open-source product catalogs have been merged into a single "apparel"
  catalog (see projects/fashioncatalog/scripts/mapper)
- most images are from original catalogs but some have been created using openAI
- That 'merged' catalog is now used as first 'input' to this updater process
  (dated pa_en_full_04012024.jsonl, tsv)
- previously generated catalog can be updated, including:
    - add new products (along with their attributes, images, ...)
    - remove specific products (using some criteria)
    - add/remove attributes
    - change specific attribute values

Script structure:
 - there is a main 'updaterMain.py' (and associated updaterConstants.py)
 - there is a 'revision' specific updater (eg, revisionV8.py and associated revisionConstantsV8.py)
   - revision updater class is derived from a "base" class (revisionBase.py)
   - revision specific updates are handled in revision-specific script (eg, revisionV8.py)
   - the revision specific class is loaded (instantiated) in updaterMain and actual revision occurs in that class
    - this approach helps to keep different revisions isolated from each other

 - a sub-directory 'data' in turn has 'input' and 'output'
   - input has previous catalog (which is to be updated), along with category .tsv
   - revision script writes its output to data/output

 - an 'injected_av_map.tsv' is also created.
    - it can be used by other people to change attribute values (eg, style)
    - the script then reads this 'edited' av-map and adjusts attribute value as edited

File naming convention
 - output files are .jsonl catalog file, list of attributes in the catalog
 - jsonl file name (example): pa_en_full_<date>.jsonl
    - pa: 'pacificapparel'
    - en: 'english'
    - full: not-a-subset (subset could be used later to build catalogs in other languages)
    - date: mmddyyyy (eg, 07102024) 

Convenience files
 - scripts to ingest and index generated catalog
    - can be used to ingest/index in staging or prod
 - these scripts are in data/output 
    - keep_ingestbyapi_APPAREL.py
    - keep_indexbyapi_APPAREL.py
    - keep_ingestbyapi_FASHION.py
    - keep_indexbyapi_FASHION.py

    -- "FASHION" is internal test account to verify generated catalog is OK/not-OK/...



